Slice off the secret box authentication
tag (first 16 bytes) and prepend the body
Enclose the body length and body
authentication tag in another secret box.
This secret box becomes the header.
Secret boxes put a 16-byte tag onto the
front of messages so that tampering can
be detected when the box is opened.
This tag is being shown now because it needs
to be sliced off and put inside the header.
